Mauritius Medical Tourism to Advance 36% in 2011, Board of Investment Says

-- B y   K a m l e s h   B h u c k o r y
-- 
2011-03-01T16:08:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-01/mauritius-medical-tourism-to-advance-36-in-2011-board-of-investment-says.html
Mauritius expects the number of
foreign patients seeking medical care on the Indian Ocean island
nation to increase 36 percent this year from 2010, the Board of
Investment said.  The number may increase to 15,000, the Port Louis-based
board said in an e-mailed statement today following a survey of
healthcare providers.  “Mauritius has set itself a target of attracting 100,000
foreign patients by 2020,” and to contribute about $1 billion
annually to the economy, according to the statement  The main source of patients was Madagascar with 28 percent,
followed by Seychelles, Reunion,  France  and  South Africa , it
said. Foreign patients being treated in Mauritius stood at 1,000
in 2005, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kamlesh Bhuckory in Port Louis via Johannesburg at 
